data.title: Alexander Cambridge, 1st Earl of Athlone (1874
data.meta_description: The sitter was born Prince Alexander of Teck, the youngest son of Frances, Duke of Teck and Mary Adelaide, Duchess of Teck; he was the brother of Queen Mary. Educated at Eton and the Royal Military College Sandhurst, in 1904 he married Princess Alice of Albany.  He relinquished his German title as Prince of Teck in 1917 and took the family name of Cambridge, becoming a member of peerage as the 1st Earl of Athlone.  He served as an Army officer, and in 1923 he was appointed governor-general of...
